Eg the description of the wheels and brakes were very simplistic, Rory would normally state the tyre size and profile and the diameter of brakes etc etc. if you're planning to use Alex as for lower tier car marketing style videos, it'll work I reckon. But I assume most of us watch the performance car type videos WANTING to know the small details. And the lack of any specifics other than 'its good and it's fast' wouldn't cut it for me in future videos to be honest.

You need to test this car on Scottish roads. I have a Macan S and it handles like a pig on a waterbed on the roads in Perthshire. It's like driving a bouncy castle and when you put it in Sport mode it feels like the tyres are made of concrete. Porsche cannot have  developed this car properly for it to drive this way. The steering is devoid of feedback or feel. It's not quite the worst car I've driven (that was my dad's Morris Marina) but by a long way it's the worst Porsche I've had. I cannot see how making if faster would help as I have to drive it well below the speed limit just to avoid getting sea sick. My BMW 530 was way better on the same roads and my wife's Mini Cooper would leave it for dead. Save your money. Don't buy one. And it rattles non stop, which Porsche cannot fix. Pile of poo.

She made a pretty bad first impression on me. The first thing she does is disrespect rory, the person that made this channel succesfull, i know it is meant as a joke but it comes across as very condescending. She tells him that she is better and a professional and the tone of her voice in that conversation seems to show her extreme drive to be succesfull wherever she works. I can tell she dislikes being new on the channel because of her passive agression when rory said it was his channel. She seems to get triggered and started telling him she was better than him. Even pushed him trying to show she is not afraid. 

I think there are others ways to do your first impression, like respect rory and be thankfull for the opportunity the channel gives you. Just be respectfull and kind to a person every viewer likes. Give the audience some time to get to know your soft side. Later in the relastionship between rory and alex she can show a bit of teasing. And that teasing can develop into a fun communicationstyle between the two.
